---
import { Colors } from "../../util/Colors";
import SkillsCard from "./SkillsCard.astro";
---

<div
  class="flex flex-col justify-evenly items-center lg:flex-row lg:space-x-20"
>
  <img
    class="rounded-lg border-black border-4 border-b-8 border-r-8 aspect-square md:h-96"
    src="./images/1162430_336.jpg"
  />
  <div class="w-fit lg:w-2/5 flex flex-col grow md:max-w-xl">
    <div>
      <p class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-wide font-playfair pb-5">
        {"What are my skills"}<span class="font-extrabold pl-2">?</span>
      </p>
      <p class="font-poppins text-base font-medium">
        In these years of my <span
          class="font-extrabold border-b-2 border-violet-500 text-violet-600"
          >programming</span
        > journey,I have encountered many frameworks and languages,all of them were
        great and were really fun to work with. But at the end I really liked with
        these two:
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex space-y-5 flex-col py-5 grow font-poppins">
      <SkillsCard
        primary="Mobile Develpoment"
        secondary={"Mobile has become a must in these days, thus creating a mobile application is really benificiary.I love to create mobile apps using flutter,it's one of the greatest framework for creating cross-platform apps.I am too learning android framework with kotlin"}
        image="./images/10301602_4412951.jpg"
        background={Colors.teal}
      />
      <SkillsCard
        primary="Backend Development"
        secondary={"I love creating API's and integrate them with a frontend app.The language of choice for creating backend in python.I have worked with the top 3 web framwork ie, Django ,Flask and Fastapi"}
        image="./images/4103163_1032.jpg"
        background={Colors.pink}
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
